,Recommended,510510,32744176,Posted: 24 June,all,Ramingo,"So, with the summer sale here, I thought, why not buy this game. And here, as someone who has played since SmackDown! vs RAW 2009, is my review.GameplayThe gameplay has improved somewhat since 2k15 (haven't played 16), and the moves are sold much better by the wrestlers than before. But still there's some buggy stuff going around. I had this match with John Cena vs Daniel Bryan and somehow it became Bryan vs Tyson Kidd with me as Cena just running around not able to pin one of the two. Also some moves are still glitchy, but besides those bugs, the gameplay is rather good.GraphicsI understand that you need a good pc for this, but as someone who can play GTA V on High/Ultra settings on stable 60-70 fps, Dying Light on High or Mirror's Edge Catalyst on High without a single stutter, I'm pretty dissapointed that this game just can't run properly on my rig on High settings. And even when I have adjusted the graphics so that it runs on 60 fps, it still doesn't feel like 60 fps sometimes. Also the fact that the fps kinda drops outside the rings pretty bad.RosterRoster is good, without DLC's aswell. Creating CAW's is fun, but I miss a lot of NORMAL hairstyles and stuff we had before. Also the body art has been minimalized a lot.UniverseBetter and worse than before. Nothing much to say about it.MyCareerHaven't played yet.Overall Result7,3 out of 10Recommended, but beefy PC is necessary."
