ight click the game > Properties > Local Files > Browse Local Files > Right click WWE2k17_x64.exe > Properties > Compatibility > Check 'Run program as Admin' Box > Apply > Right click .exe > Send to desktop.- CHOOSE the correct processor (I use Nvidia)>>> Launch Nvidia Control Panel > Manage 3D settings > Program Settings Tab > Select the game (If not there ADD the game) > Select correct Processor > Apply > Close_________________________RANDOM CRASHING!!!wtf is it - Game crashes randomly... lolwtf do I do:- CHANGE the game's priority>>> While in game, alt+tab out > Open Task Manager > Go to Details Tab > Right click wwe2k17 > Set priority to HIGHNOTE: Even after doing this, the game still crashes specifically when going to edit custom superstars again when you've just edited them (even after 3-4 matches).________________- In my honest opinion, it's a great game. Much more polished than 2k16, however some CHANGES, additions, and REMOVAL of certain features are... Questionable.- Also the submission minigame was changed slightly so... heads up. lol- Do I recommend the game? YES!- Should you wait for a patch? YES!- What if you don't give a ♥♥♥♥ what I think? YES!>>> Get the game, just take precautions and be aware of these issues.Cheers."
