,Not Recommended,510510,33102217,Posted: 1 July,all,Avonar,"It's not a bad game all in all but the multitude of bugs mean that I just cannot recommend this.First and foremost, crashes. I get crashes during matches and Create a Moveset. Sometimes it works fine, other times I have played the same match 3 or 4 times in a row. This is just ridiculous.Second, the My Career mode has some major failings, first and foremost the authority stuff. You get a challenge to complete during the match, put on a 4 star match, perform 2 finishers, things like that. It is an interesting take...in theory. Unfortunately there is a massive disconnect between the challenge and the gameplay. You are sometimes told to lose a match, which would make it seem more like an actual wrestling match except for the fact that losing a fact has no positives. You lose points in your rivalry, you get much fewer upgrade points, and there is no story benefits either. And that's not including the ones that just don't work. I have been told to win by DQ with no way of doing it, the opponent refused to use a weapon or anything. I have been told to win with green health, and then be attacked in a scripted cutscene making this impossible...it's bad.My Universe works...kind of. It automates the matches, and editing them will throw off rivalry plans, title matches etc, I never felt like I was in full control.I also don't like the VC Points. You get them at the end of each match, and you can use them to upgrade a My Career character, buy skills/managers and also unlock movesets. The best movesets are very expensive, and all they give you are a small number of famous WWE wresters' moves. The moves are all ranked A-D so the ones you really like and want to use might be the worst ones, while the best ones you don't want to use. The VC points are also universal across every My Career mode and My Universe mode, so spending them in one gamemode means you can't use them in another.On the upside, I do like the gameplay. It usually feels fairly fluid, you can't reverse every single thing so it gives an element of strategy, however it is not hard by any means. It's a nice, mindless game really. It's a game with potential, however as it seems not to have ever been patched it is never going to realise that potential. A buy on sale if you really want a PC wrestling game."
