ion VC just to get your Wrestler maxed out when you get 9000 VC per match and a low amount from T-Shirt sales only when you have a shirt is questionable to say the least.Also you can only import your own music via third party tools and the Roster is questionable, it's the biggest licensed one (otherwise Fire Pro with up to 500 wrestlers still takes the cake since all there wasn't licensed were the names) but you have to wonder why they decided to add Road Dogg and Billy Gunn but remove X-Pac (was in 2K16) so you can't have a proper D-Generation X. The Freebirds as Hall of Fame members lack Terry ""Bam Bam"" Gordy with the HoF Showcase match only being a Tag-Team match because of that and they removed the Honky Tonk Man but added Greg Valentine this year, so we can't have Rhythm 'n Blues from 1990?Gameplay wise it's the same as the last 3 years, button combination and reversals with some QTE's thrown in. The graphics are also basically the same but  the system requirements are higher with some weird slowdowns especially when climbing the cage in a Steel Cage match.The commentators are horrible and again i wonder how that can be. NBA 2K has some great commentating, the best in sports games today, so 2K and Visual Concepts who work on both games should bring in the same quality to WWE...yet, they don't. You get the same repetitive lines over and over and over again and the commentators blast you for doing the same move twice in one match, even if it's just a punch!The licensed songs are abysmal except for Sabbath's Paranoid, the Wrestler Themes are only available in highly shortened versions so they sometimes loop thorugh long entrances but vial mods you can iject the proper songs and also replace some fantasy themes with themes for your CAWOnline so far has been a bit more stable than in 2K16, at least i hadn't had  desync so far and with a friend or multiple friends it is fun.Is the game worth it? I guess for the 70% off currently it might be worth if you like wrestling. Personally i decided that this was my last WWE 2K game until they make the career worthwhile and bring the gameplay closer to something that is fun and not just a reversal and qte-fest."
