76561197988113155,Recommended,510510,30696682,Posted: 23 March,all,SAF,"I liked WWE 2k16 a lot, you can check out my review on that version, it wasn't perfect, but it was the best wrestling game in the last several years. Fast-forward to 2k17 and not a lot has changed, which is good, but I'll explain why this version is even better for me.First off, I highly recommend the game if you like wrestling games. It's one of my favorites of all time, but if you didn't like 2k16 for whatever reason, you probably won't like 2k17, but it depends. CAW, which is my favorite feature in any wrestling game, is better in most ways in 2k17 than it has ever been.I 've created about 30 wrestlers so far, so I've used it extensively. They've added a lot to every catagory (hair styles, clothes, teeth, etc...) but one HUGE disappoint for me is that you still cannot create little people. I would love to create a much shorter wrestler, but the shortest you can go is only 5'6"", which continues to bum me out year after year. How hard would it be to extend the range of heights to under 5 foot??? I want to make a dwarf dammit!Aside from that, you pick from body types and pre-made parts (arms, legs, chest, etc...) instead of using a body slider. This is a step back as it doesn't let me have the customization we once had. Gone are the days of making an incredibly huge breasted thin woman. Not that I create that type of CAW or anything...other than that, the CAW has improved in every possible way=more of everything!It still irratates me that Yukes always does this year after year. Adds something, takes away. No create-a-finisher either, in this version, but next year they'll tout it as a ""brand new never before seen feature!!!"" Love/hate relationship when it comes to Yukes.The graphics are a bit better, but some wrestlers actually look like♥♥♥♥♥♥compared to others. Not a big deal to me because I usually just use my CAWs, but you can tell some wrestlers got a little more tlc than others. Audio is pretty much poop as  Diddy's song selection is downright ""weird"" for a wrestling video game, but again, no issue, as I turn on most every wrestler's entrace as my menu music (jukebox). The commentary has been recycled for the last 5 years but it doesn't really bother me much, I'm more in this game for the actual gameplay.The gameplay is about the same as 2k16, but with slight improvments! A 2nd opportunity to reverse on certain moves, the option to change the god-awful submission system to more of a classic button mashing submission system, and the ""Break Out"" feature after the match, which allows you to further pummel a wrestler you have already beaten. I LOVE these new features. ! The game pace is still more geared towards simulation, so expect slower pacing, not blazing fast arcade pacing. Although you can change some options, and that gets us to my final point...If you don't like the game and you think it's utter ****, for the love of all that is holy and sacred in this world, CHANGE THE SETTINGS!!!! and change the balancing!!!!! I cannot emphasize this enough!!! I really did not enjoy this game that much until I changed some settings. The pacing was too slow and the time the wrestlers were stunned was way too long, which made for a very boring match! After tweaking the balance, I'm good to go, and now have a bit faster paced matches. That may not be your cup of tea, but there is plenty of settings you can change to make the match more fun for you, whatever that may be. Guys/gals, seriously, I've been playing wrestling games since NES, the settings in these Yukes titles can make a big difference.In closing wwe 2k17 is the best we have yet on PC just don't go in expecting a No Mercy as everyone seems to do, every friggin year...ugh...in ways it's better than No Mercy,, the CAW feature alone will keep you entertained. As far as issues with crashes, rare, in my playtime only 3 times so far and it was during load, not during the middle of anything, so I never lost any data. Runs smooth maxed 60fps 24/7 on my system.***I do not play any wrestling games online mode after atrocious matches I tried to have in a much earlier version, I believe it was wwe 10 or something, spamming the same move was the name of the game. Know going in that online in any wrestling game is a low priority and it should never be bought for that, it usually does not work well at all with many people picking a wrestler who is fast and can pull off the same exact fast move, over and over, so I could care less about MP in a wrestling game"
