gh menus.then we get to the ""pagentry"" of the WWE.  this game tries to show all of it.  are you familiar with the press conferences in NBA 2K?  know how you wish you could just skip that and get to the next game?  in WWE you must go out of your way to speak to the crowd, or your character's stats will suffer.  every guy has an entrance.  all the stuff you normally press start to skip in NBA just takes four times as long here.  i want to play the game, not look at how pretty the lights are when some guy comes walking towards the ring.the fights are varied, which is definitely a positive compared to MMA games.  there are 4 way brawls, 3 on 3, 2 on 2, and others.  this definitely helps during the course of a long career.the game isn't horrible by any means.  as stated it runs perfectly on my comp.  the controls are tight, for what they are.  graphics are great but nowadays i can't ever complain about that.  however once you've dealt with all the menus, light shows, talking trash at other wrestlers and actually get into a match it just isn't fun to play."
