,Recommended,510510,30005041,Posted: 18 February,all,Frendle,"So the last rasslin' game I played was WWE 2k15, and this is an immense improvement over that.  I played a lot of PS1/2/3/4 rasslin games too, and I think with 2k17 they are finally getting back to the expectations that those titles from many years ago set for me.THE GOOD:- all the mini-games are great, I'm a big fan of the submission system.  They're not too complicated but they feel skillfull and thankfully there's no button mashing.  No more being at the mercy of simple dice rolls to determine the outcome of the match, now I can get good at stuff and feel like I actually won or lost.  It makes the whole thing feel more gamey.- character abilities so far have led a very satisfying air of strategy to matches.  It's nothing too complex, but I do find myself using strategies to get 5 star matches while avoiding a loss.  This whole part feels a bit more fleshed out and better thought out than it did in 2k15.- the game is a lot more clear about how to get 5 star matches, and it lets you know how well you're doing on that during the match.  This goes hand in hand with my previous comment because it really shapes my choices during the match.  If I'm on the verge of getting five stars I might pull some risky stuff for a great match and try to be clever with the use of my wrestler's abilities to mitigate the risk.  Sometimes it backfires on me and I have to adjust to a losing situation - have had some very exciting match endings because of this!- character creater has so many options it's silly.  In fact, some of the things you can put on your character are kind of silly.  Everything looks great too - I've basically made the same guy in every rasslin' game I ever played, but this time around he looks the coolest!  In fact, he looks more like an actual guy than some of the actual wrestlers in the game do - first time I've seen created wrestlers look more high def than the real guys lol- Career mode is hugely improved.  Things started kicking off immediately - a few matches in I was slowly on my way to a title, and part of a rivalry.  Lots of little interactions happen in between of matches as well, and overall you get a lot more options to interact with your career.  Compared to the nothing that was the 2k15 career mode, this is pretty fantastic and was the one part of the game where I really wanted to see some improvement.THE OKAY- I'm a bit half and half on the reversal system.  It feels like having more reversals than your opponent is just such a hard numerical advantage because once he's done reversing, you still can.  End result: you are in charge of the match every time an exchanges of reversals end. I would have liked to see some more mechanics that allow you to get reversals back to sort of break this pattern.  Certain reversals being able to lockout your opponents reversals temporarily is a start - but again, works better for the wrestler who has more reversals.- the promo system, where your character walks out to the ring and flaps their jaw, or gets into some verbal sparring with another wrestler is on the one hand a really exciting mechanic for the game.  However, the choices feel really cryptic like the little chunk of preview text you choose doesn't always let you know what your character is really going to say.  The fact that you have to match up both your general tone on various subjects along with a face/heel image in order to get a strong reaction out of the current type of crowd means those choices need to be pretty clear.  I pick something that I think is gonna be a nice friendly face comment for a family friendly crowd, and next thing you know I'm being a huge heel.THE BAD- character creater doesn't have body morphing sliders ( or if there are any I haven't found them ) which reduces the ability to really fine tune your created wrestlers.- I have pretty decent hardware and I had to fiddle with graphics settings to get the game running smoothly.  I still basically have graphics settings maxed though, so everything looks fantastic.  Overall it runs great though - feels generalyl more responsive than 2k15."
